This is a lovely loop trail with gorgeous views of the salt marsh, outer beach, and ocean.

Accessibility: Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need all-terrain tires or adaptive/motorized equipment for the surface type and grade after about 0.6 miles when going counterclockwise. Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need assistance in the steeper section or to avoid it for safety. 

The most accessible portion of the trail is the first about 0.6 miles when going counterclockwise on the Red Maple Swamp Trail.

Accessible Parking:
Number of designated accessible spaces: 3 at the trailhead;
Number of van-accessible spaces with access aisles: 2;
Parking lot surface: paved.

Trail Details:
Trail surface: paved asphalt, gravel, a natural surface (dirt, sand), wooden boardwalk with edge barriers;
Average trail width: 6 feet;
Estimated average grade category: mostly gentle (5% or less) with steeper section at about 1.1 miles when going counterclockwise.

The first part of the trail is a paved road but turns into a wooden natural surface trail. It is not well marked after the paved section ends. 

Accessibility: Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need all-terrain tires or adaptive/motorized equipment for the surface type and grade after about 0.5 miles. Visitors using wheelchairs, mobility equipment, or strollers may need assistance in the steeper sections or to avoid them for safety. 

The most accessible portion of the trail is the first about 0.5 miles when going south. 

Accessible Parking:
Parking lot surface: gravel;
There do not appear to be any designated accessible parking spaces within 1.0 miles of the trailhead.

