The first 2.5+ miles of this trail run on the edge of the reservoir at water level. It’s a peaceful and serene setting. The only things you hear are the wind-swept waves lapping at the shore and the birds. You can make it a loop by going away from the shore and walking on a ridge before circling back to rejoin the featured trail. Parking is limited; there's space for three cars. You can also park on the shoulder of Old North Dana Road.

